IssueDetail.Title_Description:
StructLayout(LayoutKind.Sequential) is not respected in some cases Consider the following repro code.
Here structs `S0<S2A>` and `S0<S2B>` are expected to be layed out in memory with the same sequence of fields (even though `bool` may require more bytes than `byte`). 

```
