IssueDetail.Description:
From #18926 the JIT mostly does an impressively good job of optimizing this code:
```cs
	public class SpanTest
	{
		private struct Data { public int a b c d; }
		private static Data _data = default;

		public void IncrementA() => IncrementWrapper(MemoryMarshal.CreateSpan(ref _data.a 4));
		[MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining)]
		public static void IncrementWrapper(Span<int> span)
		{
			if ((uint)span.Length < 4) throw new IndexOutOfRangeException();
			Increment(ref span[0]);
		}
		private static void Increment(ref int val) => val++;
	}
```

```asm
