IssueDetail.Description:
@petejohanson commented on [Sun May 06 2018](https://github.com/dotnet/core/issues/1503)
# Alpine docker image segfault when run from a host system w/ SELinux execheap enforcement
From my Fedora laptop attempting to use the `microsoft/dotnet:2.1-sdk-alpine` docker image as soon as the 'dotnet' tool is invoked it immediately segfaults within the container and the "SELinux Alert Browser" notes that the dotnet process attempted execheap access which triggered a denial.
The same is true if I attempt to use a non-alpine docker image for my build and use the alpine runtime docker image.
# General
Host OS: Fedora 28 Docker image: microsoft/dotnet:2.1-sdk-alpine (70f0d46441ae)
Build output:
``` [peter@respect:~/git/fore-scorer/api] docker build . Sending build context to Docker daemon 32.96MB Step 1/22 : FROM node:8.9-alpine as COUCHDB_COMPILE ---> 144aaf4b1367 Step 2/22 : WORKDIR /opt/couchdb-compile ---> Using cache ---> a73eb9708461 Step 3/22 : COPY ./package.json ./package-lock.json ./ ---> Using cache ---> bbe9529d56c7 Step 4/22 : RUN npm install ---> Using cache ---> 8fe6cdf59401 Step 5/22 : COPY ./api/couchdb ./api/couchdb ---> Using cache ---> 92a45a0c55db Step 6/22 : RUN npm run couchdb-compile ---> Using cache ---> 101eb5d568bd Step 7/22 : FROM microsoft/dotnet:2.1-sdk-alpine AS BUILD_IMAGE ---> 70f0d46441ae Step 8/22 : ENV APP_HOME=/opt/fore-scorer ---> Using cache ---> beb01f7d9dd6 Step 9/22 : WORKDIR $APP_HOME ---> Using cache ---> 9e39bca48f48 Step 10/22 : COPY ./api/api.fsproj . ---> e4da0674d419 Step 11/22 : RUN dotnet restore ---> Running in 15e922a4bcfd Segmentation fault (core dumped) The command '/bin/sh -c dotnet restore' returned a non-zero code: 139 ```
